items.name: Ferrari Testarossa
items.description:
The Ferrari Testarossa (Type F110) is a 12-cylinder mid-engine sports car manufactured by Ferrari, which went into production in 1984 as the successor to the Ferrari Berlinetta Boxer. The Pininfarina-designed car was originally produced from 1984 until 1991, with two model revisions following the end of Testarossa production called the 512 TR and F512 M, which were produced from 1992 until 1996. Including revised variations, almost 10,000 cars in total were produced, making it at the time one of the most mass-produced Ferrari models.[2]

The Testarossa is a two-door coupé that premiered at the 1984 Paris Auto Show.[3] All versions of the Testarossa were available with a rear-mounted, five-speed manual transmission. The rear mid-engine design (engine between the axles but behind the cabin) keeps the centre of gravity in the middle of the car, which increases stability and improves the car's cornering ability, and thus results in a standing weight distribution of 40% front: 60% rear.[4]

The original Testarossa was re-engineered for the 1992 model year and was introduced as the 512 TR (TR meaning TestaRossa), at the Los Angeles Auto Show, effectively as a completely new car,[2] and an improved weight distribution of 41% front, 59% rear.[5] Another new variant called the F512 M was introduced at the 1994 Paris Auto Show.[2] The car dropped the TR initials and added the M which in Italian stood for modificata, or translated to modified, and was the final version of the Testarossa,[2][3] which continued its predecessor's weight distribution improvement of 42% front, 58% rear. The F512 M was Ferrari's last vehicle that featured the flat-12 engine.

The Testarossa is a recognized cultural icon of the 1980s, and was popularized by media including the 1984 television series Miami Vice and Sega's 1986 video game Out Run.

items.name: dvPortrait
items.description:
These models generates portraits! They produce photorealistic, medium length portrait generations with relatively easy prompts, and there's two dedicated versions: one trained on stock photos of men and one on women. Both use the same trigger prompt: "dvPortrait" so put that close to the beginning of the prompt.

Each model was trained using The Last Ben Fast Dream Booth on ~20 high resolution, licensed SFW stock photos, at 768px resolution.

All example images generated using Automatic1111 at 768x768 resolution. They all include prompt and sampling data, and here is an example prompt structure for this model, try adjusting the words in italics for different types of people.

Example prompt:
(dvPortrait style:0.7), (beautiful woman:1.2), (85mm:0.9), f1.8, (skin pours:1.0), messy hair, shadows, dynamic pose, professional portrait photography, subtle details, muted, desaturated, low contrast, (hdr:0.7), canon 5D

Negative:
soft, blurry, out of focus, poor quality, hands, deformed, text, type, watermark, logo, underdeveloped, ((pixelated)), (compressed), naked, overexposed

Settings:
Steps: 15, Sampler: Euler, CFG scale: 7, Face restoration: CodeFormer, Size: 768x768, Model: dvPortrait

If you use the models: please leave a review and post some of the images created.

items.name: Monmusu Alice 16th
items.description:
LORA trained on Alipheese Fateburn XVI (Alice) from MGQ.

Training based on ingame CG, fanart and v0.2 generated good images (curated with inpaint for better detail accuracy, eg tattoo shape and clothing)

Trained on NED and tested also with AIOMonsterGirls and anything-v4.5.

Related to v0.3:

This version is less overfitted than the previous, while focusing more accurately on alice's details.

Hence it should be much easier to obtain good pictures without seed-hunting and should also be adaptable to way more models.

Suggested weights:

  • 0.65~0.8: For more photorealistic, look and less bound to the ingame details

  • 0.8~1.0: To more easily reproduce all of her details, especially for her lamia form

Her monster form features are tied to the monster_girl and lamia tags, but sometime specifying purple_skin as well might help.

Also the tattoo and black_gloves should now be more ingrained in the lora, but not overfitted, (should be easier to obtain on high lora weight, but can be specified as a tag for lower weights). (It is possible to get the shape of her tattoos identical to the original, but without manually priming it and going with inpaint, it is still not super consistent)

Using the skirt prompt and higher lora weights should help get her skirt closer to the original.

I also suggest using the negative tag symmetry to help reproduce her look (eg tattoo, flower and skirt are totally non-symemtryic), and legs when going for her lamia form (atleast for solo images).

As for the previous version, when going for the lamia form i would also suggest using a 0.1~0.3 of the anime lamia LORA. You can get good lamia stuff without, but the waist/tail connection is not consistent.

TODO for v1.0:

Try to also accurately reproduce many of her various monstergirl type feature. Not sure how likely it is to do all in a single LORA or if a more specific inpaint one is warranted.

items.name: Power LoRA [72MB] (With Inpaint Eyes)
items.description:
Power LoRA becase I wasnt satisfied with the others. Loads of NSFW refs, because cmon, who are we kidding. Trained on a fair few dymanic images, but also some of the toilet based ones, so should be very easy to get toilet based images.

Trained on Anything v4.0.

INPAINT EYES - Can fairly accurately capture the character, but the big thing that I wanted was the eyes. So while sometimes the eyes may be a little strange, all you need to do is send it to inpaint, and (with the LoRA) use 'cross-shaped pupils, symbol-shaped pupils'. Paint the entire eyes, not just the pupil, use only masked, reduce the quality down to 512x512, and a denoise of around 0.5.

The teeth are also sometimes hard to get good. You can also do the same Eye inpaint steps for the mouth if you wish.


Weighting should be good around 0.7-0.8.

PLEASE NOTE THAT A LOT OF THE REF IMAGES ARE INPAINTED, THUS MISSING THE ORIGINAL METADATA

Enjoy

items.name: Reaper (Overwatch) LORA
items.description:
My twelfth Overwatch LORA. Both masked and unmasked.

  • Masked - reaper, skull mask, hood up, armor, ammunition belt, greaves, gauntlets

  • Unmasked- gabrielreyes, wool hat, military uniform

  • Miscellaneous - shotgun, dual wielding, bandolier, shotgun shells, armored robe (this one gives Plague Doctor looking armor, not that great though)

Checked strength range is 0.5-0.9. Unmasked look is a bit plastiky on higher weights.

If you liked my work, you can donate here.

Inpaint guide: if face\mask on full body shots comes out deformed\not detailed enough - it's easily fixed with single inpaint, whole process takes half a minute. Press "Send to inpaint" button under generated image, mask the face area with drawing tool, choose DDIM sampler, set "Inpaint area" to "only masked", and set denoising strength to 0,5. Press generate and you done!


Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.

Trained on Anything V4.5 with anime.vae.pt and CLIP Skip 2.

Samples are 512x768, without HighRes.fix, using OrangeCocoa 50/50 Mix , with OrangeMix VAE, and using EasyNegative embedding, CLIP Skip 2.
